                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d79">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 Pacific War/35</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Statement by President Roosevelt on June 5, 1942</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1942-06-05">June 5, 1942</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>Authoritative reports are reaching this Government of the use by Japanese armed
                    forces in various localities of China of poisonous or noxious gases. I desire to
                    make it unmistakably clear that, if Japan persists in this inhuman form of
                    warfare against China or against any other of the United Nations, such action
                    will be regarded by this Government as though taken against the United States,
                    and retaliation in kind and in full measure will be meted out. We shall be
                    prepared to enforce complete retribution. Upon Japan will rest the
                    responsibility.</p>
            </div>
